      <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
        <from>MADAM SPEAKER</from>
        <p>MADAM SPEAKER : Order, please. We'll now commence with the daily routine.</p>
      </speech>
      <debateSection>
        <heading>PRESENTING REPORTS OF COMMITTEES</heading>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MADAM SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MADAM SPEAKER : The honourable Minister of Justice.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#4fe6044a-d86e-4a24-bc37-127add6fe273">
          <from>HON. ROSS LANDRY</from>
          <p>HON. ROSS LANDRY : Madam Speaker, as Chairman of the Committee on Law Amendments, I am directed to report that the committee has met and considered the following bills:</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MADAM SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MADAM SPEAKER : Ordered that these bills be referred to the Committee of the Whole House on Bills.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#c59d09ae-4388-42ee-9011-29467c4fdc25">
          <from>MS. MICHELE RAYMOND</from>
          <p>MS. MICHELE RAYMOND : Madam Speaker, as Chairman of the Committee on Private and Local Bills, I am directed to report that the committee has met and considered the following bills:</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MADAM SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MADAM SPEAKER : Ordered that these bills be referred to the Committee of the Whole House on Bills.</p>
        </speech>
      </debateSection>
      <debateSection>
        <heading>TABLING REPORTS, REGULATIONS AND OTHER PAPERS</heading>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MADAM SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MADAM SPEAKER : The honourable Minister of the Public Service Commission.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#4c929028-e1d5-46a9-9075-8620e1ec2e77">
          <from>HON. FRANK CORBETT</from>
          <p>HON. FRANK CORBETT : Madam Speaker, I beg leave to table the Annual Report of the Civil Service Disclosure of Wrongdoing Regulations and Policy, 2010-2011.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MADAM SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MADAM SPEAKER : The report is tabled.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#ca9aa78a-99fe-43e6-b6a7-daae19a39ce9">
          <from>HON. GRAHAM STEELE</from>
          <p>HON. GRAHAM STEELE : Madam Speaker, I beg leave to table Nova Scotia's Jobs and Building Plan, the 2012-2013 Capital Plan.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MADAM SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MADAM SPEAKER : The plan is tabled.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#ca9aa78a-99fe-43e6-b6a7-daae19a39ce9">
          <from>HON. GRAHAM STEELE</from>
          <p>HON. GRAHAM STEELE : Madam Speaker, in response to a question raised during Question Period last week, I am pleased to table the financial statement for the Victims' Assistance Fund for 2011.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MADAM SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MADAM SPEAKER : The statement is tabled.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#4fe6044a-d86e-4a24-bc37-127add6fe273">
          <from>HON. ROSS LANDRY</from>
          <p>HON. ROSS LANDRY : Madam Speaker, I beg leave to table an amendment to the Nova Scotia Civil Procedure Rules, dated December 9, 2011.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MADAM SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MADAM SPEAKER : The amendment is tabled.</p>
        </speech>
      </debateSection>
      <debateSection>
        <heading>STATEMENTS BY MINISTERS</heading>
